author: LZA RAE
text: My parents arrived in MD safely from NC. Procedure is at 730a. I’m nervous as hell but I’m ready to get this over with. My moms had a hysterectomy at 43y/o. It took forever to heal. I’m 41y/o, not sure if fibroids are genetically passed on.

author: LZA RAE
text: These growths have literally been stealing my blood, proteins, organs, weight and all the things that I need to keep me healthy. I had no idea fibroids had that much power. I tried natural healing, changed my diet. It didn’t help.

author: LZA RAE
text: I was just sitting here thinkin, dayum I actually been walking around with 25 small golf ball and grapefruit sized growths in my body for who knows how long. That’s wild af!!! Smh. The physical sustainability of a woman’s body is so amazing.
